# LiveScore HTTP layer

## Files

- `customFetch.ts` — server-side fetch compatible with generated Kubb clients; reads `LIVESCORE_*` env.
- `logged-fetch.ts` — instrumentation / logging for API calls (keep consistent when adding endpoints).
- `rate-limiter.ts` — throttle behavior; do not bypass without an explicit product reason.

## Rules

- All **browser-facing** routes must call LiveScore **only from server** code (route handlers, server components, sync scripts).
- When adding a new API consumer, reuse these wrappers instead of raw `fetch` to keys.
- If you change error handling, ensure `ApiRequestLogs` (collection) expectations stay aligned where used.

